FT  07 APR 93 / Computer plant for Cumbernauld
ELONEX, the personal computer producer, is to have its main components
manufactured at a plant to be set up in Cumbernauld near Glasgow by Cordata,
an associated company.
Cordata plans to invest Pounds 5.5m in a new 40,000 sq ft plant, which is
expected to employ 175 people.
Mimtec, the electronics manufacturer which is a subsidiary of Murray
International, a privately owned Scottish company, confirmed yesterday that
it is to set up a Pounds 20m plant at Gourock, Renfrewshire, which will
carry out subcontract work for International Business Machines. The plant
will employ 400 people.
